# Lessons (cross-project)

## Tooling Lessons

<!--
Things learned about tools that apply everywhere. Examples:
- `git reset --hard` is fast and irreversible — always create a backup branch first.
- Vitest >>> Jest for new Node projects: ESM-native, faster, less config.
- For Anthropic API: stream by default — non-stream blocks the event loop for long generations.
-->

## Process Lessons

<!--
Things learned about workflow. Examples:
- When a session runs > 1 hour without a commit, something has gone wrong.
- "I'll factor it out later" almost always means "this will be wrong forever".
- Reading the actual code beats reading the docs about the code.
-->

## Anti-patterns

<!--
Failure modes the user has been burned by. Examples:
- Don't refactor and add features in the same PR. Reviewer can't tell what changed.
- Don't `pip install` from inside a session without explicit user OK.
- Don't write fallback code for cases that can't actually happen.
-->
